title: 'Gaza ceasefire deal must allow Israel to resume fighting until its objectives are met': Benjamin Netanyahu
content: The three-phase plan, presented by US President Joe Biden in May and mediated by Qatar and Egypt, seeks to end the war and secure the release of approximately 120 Israeli hostages held in Gaza.

title: Philippines and Japan sign defence pact, with eyes on China
content: The Philippines and Japan have signed a reciprocal access agreement to deploy forces on each other's soil, enhancing military cooperation. The deal aims to address rising tensions in the Indo-Pacific region, particularly concerning China's maritime claims. Both countries are strengthening defense ties to bolster deterrence capabilities.

Landslides kill 12 on Indonesia's Sulawesi island, 18 missing
content: At least 12 died, 18 are missing after torrential rain caused a landslide in an illegal gold mine in Sumawa district, Sulawesi. Five survivors evacuated. 164 national rescue team, police, military personnel, led by Heriyanto, are searching. Thick mud, continuing rain hinder efforts. Houses, bridge damaged. Rain expected in Gorontalo, BNPB warns.
summary: At least 12 died, 18 are missing after torrential rain caused a landslide in an illegal gold mine in Sumawa district, Sulawesi. title: Nepal PM 'Prachanda' should resign immediately, demands former ally CPN-UML
content: Oli-led CPN-UML demands PM Prachanda's resignation before a July 12 confidence vote after losing Nepali Congress and JSP support. Prachanda seeks this vote under Article 100 (2) of the Nepal constitution addressed to federal parliament. Nepal had 13 governments in the last 16 years, highlighting a fragile political system.

title: Prince Harry is 'bored' in California; does not see his friends anymore because...
content: ​Harry reportedly has a pre-Meghan and post-Meghan world and the two worlds do not merge. Harry was in England in May for the 10th anniversary of the Invictus Games -- founded by Prince Harry -- but did not plan to see his friends as they are part of the pre-Meghan world which Harry hates to revisit. Harry's friends too do not reach out to the lonely prince because they feel betrayed by the way Harry wrote about his military service in his memoir 'Spare'.
